White southerners were considered to be people of class, which shows in their opinion of the post-war era. They did not need to worry about discrimination against them, because they were not discriminated against in society. Their opinion was that the black people should be happy that they had rights at all.

Black southerners were considered to be people who were not worth their salt. It was near impossible for them to actually get a job. They could not own property.

